track.name: Oprah's Bank Account (Lil Yachty & DaBaby feat. Drake)

wiki.summary: Lil Yachty, Drake, and DaBaby team up for the first time on “Oprah’s Bank Account,” a melodic trap collaboration dedicated to their significant others and named after actress and talk show host Oprah Winfrey, whose net worth is estimated at $2.6B as of this song’s release. Yachty compared the tune of this record to that of his 2016 work, referring more specifically to the first installment of his Lil Boat series, which played a huge role in bringing Yachty’s music to the mainstream at the time. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: Lil Yachty, Drake, and DaBaby team up for the first time on “Oprah’s Bank Account,” a melodic trap collaboration dedicated to their significant others and named after actress and talk show host Oprah Winfrey, whose net worth is estimated at $2.6B as of this song’s release. Yachty compared the tune of this record to that of his 2016 work, referring more specifically to the first installment of his Lil Boat series, which played a huge role in bringing Yachty’s music to the mainstream at the time. The song was eventually released on the three-year anniversary of the tape, which also marks the two-year anniversary of its follow-up Lil Boat 2. “Oprah’s Bank Account” was first teased by Yachty on Instagram on 10 January 2020 before it leaked online 19 days later with DaBaby as the only feature. It was eventually premiered with an accompanying music video and Drake’s contribution. Notably, the track’s polarizing music video sees Yachty, dressed in drag, parodying Winfrey in a similar fashion to Drake’s 2015 “Energy” music video. Read more on Last.fm.
